# .cursorrules — PA CROP Services

You are working on PA CROP Services, a Pennsylvania Commercial Registered Office Provider (CROP) business.

## Business Context
- Legal entity: PA Registered Office Services, LLC
- Domain: pacropservices.com
- Brand: PA CROP Services
- Location: Erie, Pennsylvania
- Parent: Dynasty Empire Holdings
- Status: Pre-launch (building toward first clients)

## Technology Stack
- Hosting: Vercel (static site, auto-deploys from GitHub main branch)
- Payments: Stripe (Payment Links for checkout, webhooks for automation)
- CRM/Portal: SuiteDash (client portal, CRM, billing, e-signatures, tickets)
- Automation: n8n (self-hosted at n8n.audreysplace.place — webhooks, crons, email sequences)
- Data: AiTable (event logging, lead scores, engagement tracking)
- AI Agents: OpenClaw (orchestration), Flint (VM agent on Debian at 172.20.192.46)

## Repository Structure
```
/public                    — Deployed website (Vercel serves this directory)
/business-plan             — 360-degree business plan (.docx + generator .js)
/financial-model           — 24-month P&L model (.xlsx + generator .py)
/legal                     — Service agreement, CROP registration docs
/marketing/website         — Landing page source (index.html)
/marketing/seo-articles    — 5 foundational SEO articles (.md)
/operations                — Operations bible, risk analysis, unconsidered risks
/partner-deck              — CPA/Attorney partner pitch deck (.pptx + generator .js)
/suitedash-automation      — n8n workflows, AI agents, SuiteDash niche config
  /n8n                     — Importable workflow JSON files
  /agents                  — Node.js agent modules
  /suitedash/niche_configs — pa_crop.json (complete SuiteDash configuration)
  /scripts                 — Emergency stop, connection verification
  /env                     — .env.example with all required credentials
```

## Coding Conventions
- Marketing site: Vanilla HTML/CSS/JS (NO frameworks — it's a static Vercel site)
- n8n workflows: JSON files importable via n8n UI
- Agent modules: Node.js (CommonJS require, not ES modules)
- Financial model generator: Python (openpyxl)
- Document generators: Node.js (docx library for .docx, pptxgenjs for .pptx)
- All email templates: Copy from operations/PA-CROP-Operations-Bible.md
- SuiteDash API: Headers are X-Public-ID + X-Secret-Key (NOT Authorization: Bearer)
- Stripe: Use Payment Links (not custom Checkout Sessions) for simplicity
- Git: Commit to main branch, push to origin — Vercel auto-deploys

## Key Files to Read First
1. PA-CROP-Execution-Plan.md — The master 11-phase build plan
2. PA-CROP-AI-Agent-Orchestration-Guide.md — Which tool does what
3. operations/PA-CROP-Operations-Bible.md — Every SOP, email, script
4. suitedash-automation/suitedash/niche_configs/pa_crop.json — SuiteDash configuration

## When I Ask You To "Deploy"
1. git add -A
2. git commit -m "[descriptive message]"
3. git push origin main
4. Vercel auto-deploys. No manual deployment step needed.

## PA CROP Business Rules
- Annual report deadlines: Corporations June 30, LLCs September 30, All others December 31
- CROP filing fee: $7 for for-profit entities, $0 for nonprofits
- Service tiers: Starter $79/yr, Professional $179/yr, Premium $299/yr
- Partner rate: $99/client/year (white-label)
- The 2027 dissolution deadline is the core urgency driver in all marketing content
